subject: Football
College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Levell Coppage ran for 299 yards and 3 touchdowns and Wisconsin-Whitewater forced five turnovers and shut out Mount Union in the second half to win its second consecutive N.C.A.A. Division III football national championship.
